HEADWORD: Doughface
<hw>Dough"face`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A contemptuous
nickname for a timid, yielding politician, or one who is easily
molded.</def> <mark>[Political cant, U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dough-faced</ent>⟦br⟧
